description:
Implement encoders/psychographic/ with 3 files: features.py, model.py, train.py. Read .claude/agents/encoder-specialist/AGENT.md and encoders/psychographic/SPEC.md first.

Key requirements:
(1) features.py — to_feature_vector(PsychographicVector) → 22-dim tensor; one-hot vocabularies fixed at training time and persisted to data/synthetic/psych_vocab.json; impute years_buying_category=None with median 5;
(2) model.py — MLP architecture [22→64→128] with ReLU and Dropout(0.2);
(3) train.py — supervised classification objective; split by participant_id; log to MLflow with tag modality=psychographic;
(4) also create tests/encoders/psychographic/__init__.py and tests/encoders/psychographic/test_psychographic_encoder.py — tests must pass before closing.

Acceptance: uv run pytest tests/encoders/psychographic/ passes; strategy recovery >75%.

Implement encoders/text/ with 1 file: embed.py. Read .claude/agents/encoder-specialist/AGENT.md and encoders/text/SPEC.md first.

Key requirements:
(1) load all-MiniLM-L6-v2 via sentence_transformers;
(2) set requires_grad=False on ALL sentence-transformer parameters before any training — verify with assert sum(p.requires_grad for p in sentence_model.parameters()) == 0;
(3) train only the linear projection layer 384→128;
(4) use dataclasses.replace() to write embeddings back to narratives.jsonl;
(5) check PersonaNarrative.embedding is None before re-embedding;
(6) log to MLflow with tag modality=text;
(7) also create tests/encoders/text/__init__.py and tests/encoders/text/test_text_encoder.py — tests must pass before closing.

Acceptance: uv run pytest tests/encoders/text/ passes; strategy recovery >70%; intra-persona cosine sim >0.6.

Implement encoders/transaction/ with 3 files: features.py, model.py, train.py. NOTE: disk already has features.py (empty stub) — this is correct; there is no tokeniser.py for this encoder. Read .claude/agents/encoder-specialist/AGENT.md and encoders/transaction/SPEC.md first.

Key requirements:
(1) features.py — to_token_vector(TransactionRecord) → 20-dim tensor (8+4+4+1+1+1+1); embedding lookups for brand_tier/channel/purchase_type built from training vocab, persisted to data/synthetic/tx_vocab.json;
(2) sort transactions most-recent-first per participant (by days_before_session ascending = oldest first → reverse so index 0 = most recent);
(3) model.py — GRU hidden_size=128, num_layers=2, dropout=0.1, batch_first=True; use pack_padded_sequence with actual sequence lengths; output = final hidden state of last layer (not mean pooling);
(4) train.py — next brand_tier prediction objective (self-supervised); split by participant_id not record; log to MLflow with tag modality=transaction;
(5) also create tests/encoders/transaction/__init__.py and tests/encoders/transaction/test_transaction_encoder.py — tests must pass before closing.

Acceptance: uv run pytest tests/encoders/transaction/ passes; next brand_tier accuracy >45%; strategy recovery probe >60%.

Implement encoders/trace/ with 3 files: tokeniser.py, model.py, train.py. Read .claude/agents/encoder-specialist/AGENT.md and encoders/trace/SPEC.md first.

Key requirements:
(1) tokeniser.py — build attribute_id and alternative_id vocabularies from traces.jsonl on first run, cache to data/synthetic/trace_vocab.json; token dim = 27 (16+8+1+1+1); CLS token prepended at index 0;
(2) model.py — transformer encoder architecture; CLS token output is the trial embedding;
(3) train.py — NT-Xent contrastive loss + auxiliary classification head weight=0.3; split by participant_id not trial_id; log all runs to MLflow with tag modality=trace; save encoder backbone weights only (not classification head);
(4) StratifiedSampler — MUST be implemented as a batch_sampler (yields lists of indices), NOT as a sampler= argument — these are mutually exclusive in DataLoader and passing a per-index sampler destroys the per-batch guarantee; the sampler must guarantee ≥2 trials per persona_id per batch; use drop_last=True to avoid tail batches that violate this guarantee; if a persona has fewer than 2 train participants × trials, oversample with replacement within that persona rather than dropping it; accept an explicit seed= parameter for reproducibility;
(5) also create tests/encoders/trace/__init__.py and tests/encoders/trace/test_trace_encoder.py — tests must pass before closing.

Acceptance: uv run pytest tests/encoders/trace/ passes; strategy recovery probe >85%.
